==German==
===Etymology===
''Kümmel'' is in this case derived from Hebrew ''[[gimel]]'', the third letter of the Hebrew alphabet, and has nothing to do with the spice [[caraway]]. A different name for this game is ''[[Dreiblatt]]'', meaning "three cards".
This is the German name for a popular "game", which is really a set-up scam known as Three Card Monte, Find the Lady or Bonneteau.
===Noun===
'''Kümmelblättchen''' ''n''
# (archaic) a kind of [[card game]]
